President Obama spoke with Indian Prime Minister Dr. Manmohan Singh to express condolences for the victims of the attack at the gurdwara in Wisconsin. He emphasized that the Sikh community is an important part of the American family and that the incident is particularly tragic because it occurred in a place of worship. Prime Minister Singh expressed gratitude for the support from the United States and praised the prompt reaction and heroism of the local police. Both leaders reaffirmed their commitment to shared values of pluralism, religious freedom, and freedom of worship.